The paper proposes a sequence-to-sequence model for ranking, which is a central task in machine learning and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the usefulness of the proposed approach in a real-world recommendation system, which suggests the relevance to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions experiments on standard ranking benchmarks, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the benchmarks involve visual data.
